HEADWORD: Tingent
<hw>Tin"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tingens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>tingere</ets> to tinge. See
<er>Tinge</er>.]</ety> <def>Having the power to tinge.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As for the white part, it appears much less enriched with the
